triples.evidence: Now, let me share what I hope you'll take away from this lecture. We're going to approach the Fourier series from a geometric perspective, starting with the idea of high-dimensional space. This means thinking about vectors, angles, distances, and inner products - not just in two or three dimensions, but in spaces with many dimensions.
